olive oil
2 clove garlic
½ Onion
1 tomato
1 cucumber
1 packet mint
½ packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 packet pork mince
1 packet Currants
1 packet tomato paste
1 sachet Middle Eastern Seasoning
¼ cup water
20 g butter (for the filling)
20 g butter (for the pastry)
1 packet filo pastry
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
drizzle white wine vinegar

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Finely chop garlic and onion (see ingredients). Slice tomato into rounds. Slice cucumber(see ingredients) into half-moons. Thinly slice mint.
• In a small bowl, combine Greek-style yoghurt and mint. Season to taste and set aside.

• Heat a large frying pan over high heat.
• Cook pork mince (no need for oil!), onion and currants, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 3-4 minutes.
• Add garlic, tomato paste and Middle Eastern seasoning and cook, until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add the water and butter (for the filling) and simmer, until slightly reduced, 2-3 minutes. Season to taste.

• In a small microwave-safe bowl, add the butter (for the filo pastry). Microwave in 10 second bursts, until melted. Lay filo pastry sheets on a dry surface and fold in half.
• Spoon pork mixture in the center of filo sheet. Fold sides over and roll into a cigar.
• Place on a lined oven tray. Repeat with remaining filo sheets and pork mixture.

• Brush cigars with the melted butter.
• Bake until golden, 15-20 minutes.

• Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine tomato, cucumber, mixed salad leaves and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Season
to taste.

• Divide Middle Eastern pork filo cigars and cucumber tomato salad between plates.
• Serve with mint yoghurt. Enjoy!